==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[terra]], ''[[land]]'' + [[firma]], ''[[solid]]'' 

===Noun===
'''terra firma'''

# a Latin expression, but often used in English, meaning "dry land", as against water. The phrase, translated into Spanish as ''[[Tierra Firma]]'', served in the 16th century as the name of the Isthmus of Panama. It is also used for the mainland around [[Venice]].
===Synonyms===
*[[dry land]]
*[[solid ground]]

